From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 18/18] winebus: Remove hidraw devices on fatal read errors.

Fast DualSense USB disconnect/reconnect cycles can leave the old hidraw fd in
the udev poll set long enough for it to repeatedly return EIO. While that stale
fd remains active, winebus can keep processing reports for the old PDO after the
new hidraw device has been created, leaving games with a connected controller
that does not respond correctly.

Treat fatal hidraw read errors as an immediate device removal signal. Stop
polling the dead fd and queue the normal bus removal event so pending reads are
completed and the stale PDO is torn down before later reconnect events expose a
fresh device.
---
 dlls/winebus.sys/bus_udev.c | 11 ++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winebus.sys/bus_udev.c b/dlls/winebus.sys/bus_udev.c
index 11111111111..22222222222 100644
--- a/dlls/winebus.sys/bus_udev.c
+++ b/dlls/winebus.sys/bus_udev.c
@@ -350,7 +350,16 @@ static void hidraw_device_read_report(struct unix_device *iface)
 
     int size = read(impl->base.device_fd, report_buffer, sizeof(report_buffer));
     if (size == -1)
-        TRACE("Read failed. Likely an unplugged device %d %s\n", errno, strerror(errno));
+    {
+        int err = errno;
+
+        TRACE("Read failed. Likely an unplugged device %d %s\n", err, strerror(err));
+        if (err == EIO || err == ENODEV || err == ENXIO || err == ESHUTDOWN)
+        {
+            stop_polling_device(iface);
+            bus_event_queue_device_removed(&event_queue, iface);
+        }
+    }
     else if (size == 0)
         TRACE("Failed to read report\n");
     else
